# API Testing Guide

## Using this file with popular API clients:
## - Postman: Import this file
## - VS Code REST Client: Install REST Client extension
## - Insomnia: Import this file

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api
@token = YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### Health Check
GET http://localhost:5000/health

---

### 1. Register User
POST {{baseUrl}}/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

---

### 2. Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

# Copy the access_token from response and update @token variable above

---

### 3. Get User Profile
GET {{baseUrl}}/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

---

### 4. Submit Mood Entry
POST {{baseUrl}}/submit-mood
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "mood": "Happy",
  "sleep_hours": 7.5,
  "journal_text": "Had a great day today! Feeling productive and energized.",
  "date": "2026-03-09"
}

---

### 5. Submit Mood Entry with Negative Sentiment
POST {{baseUrl}}/submit-mood
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "mood": "Stressed",
  "sleep_hours": 5,
  "journal_text": "Feeling overwhelmed with work. Too many deadlines and not enough time.",
  "date": "2026-03-08"
}

---

### 6. Analyze Text Only
POST {{baseUrl}}/analyze-text
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "I'm feeling anxious about the upcoming presentation. My mind keeps racing and I can't focus."
}

---

### 7. Get User Dashboard
GET {{baseUrl}}/user-dashboard
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

---

### 8. Get Mood History (Last 7 Days)
GET {{baseUrl}}/mood-history?days=7
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

---

### 9. Get Mood History (Last 30 Days)
GET {{baseUrl}}/mood-history?days=30
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

---

### 10. Get Stress Trends
GET {{baseUrl}}/stress-trends
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

---

### 11. Get Mood Categories
GET {{baseUrl}}/mood-categories

---

## Sample Test Scenarios

### Test Case 1: Happy User with Good Sleep
POST {{baseUrl}}/submit-mood
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "mood": "Happy",
  "sleep_hours": 8,
  "journal_text": "Woke up refreshed and excited for the day ahead!",
  "date": "2026-03-09"
}

# Expected: Low stress level, positive sentiment

---

### Test Case 2: Anxious User with Poor Sleep
POST {{baseUrl}}/submit-mood
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "mood": "Anxious",
  "sleep_hours": 4,
  "journal_text": "Couldn't sleep well. Worried about everything. Feeling overwhelmed.",
  "date": "2026-03-08"
}

# Expected: High stress level, negative sentiment, recommendations

---

### Test Case 3: Neutral User
POST {{baseUrl}}/submit-mood
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "mood": "Neutral",
  "sleep_hours": 7,
  "journal_text": "Just a regular day, nothing special happened.",
  "date": "2026-03-07"
}

# Expected: Medium stress level, neutral sentiment

---

### Test Case 4: Multiple Entries for Analytics
# Submit multiple mood entries with different dates to test analytics

POST {{baseUrl}}/submit-mood
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "mood": "Excited",
  "sleep_hours": 8,
  "journal_text": "Got promoted today! So happy and excited!",
  "date": "2026-03-06"
}

---

## Error Test Cases

### Invalid Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "wrong@email.com",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}

# Expected: 401 Unauthorized

---

### Missing Token
GET {{baseUrl}}/user-dashboard

# Expected: 401 Missing token

---

### Invalid Mood
POST {{baseUrl}}/submit-mood
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "mood": "InvalidMood",
  "sleep_hours": 7
}

# Expected: 400 Validation Error

---

### Invalid Sleep Hours
POST {{baseUrl}}/submit-mood
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "mood": "Happy",
  "sleep_hours": 25
}

# Expected: 400 Validation Error
